# Dev Memory OS - Railway Environment Variables Setup Guide
# These variables need to be configured in Railway dashboard

# STEP 1: Required Environment Variables (set these in Railway)
# Go to your Railway project → Variables tab → Add these:

# OpenAI API Key (REQUIRED)
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# Production Security (REQUIRED)
# API_KEY=your-secure-api-key-for-production
# JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret-min-32-chars

# CORS Configuration (REQUIRED)
# CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-railway-app.railway.app

# STEP 2: Database Variables (Railway PostgreSQL plugin provides these automatically)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
# PGHOST=...
# PGPORT=5432
# PGUSER=...
# PGPASSWORD=...
# PGDATABASE=...

# STEP 3: Optional Performance & Monitoring
# LOG_LEVEL=info
# ENABLE_VECTOR_SEARCH=true
# RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100

# STEP 4: Railway Service Configuration
# Build Command: npm run build:railway
# Start Command: npm run start:production
# Health Check Path: /health

# STEP 5: PostgreSQL Extensions Setup
# After Railway creates your PostgreSQL service, run this command:
# railway run bash -c "psql \$DATABASE_URL -c 'CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector; CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS \"uuid-ossp\";'"